Type at the shell:
    ./configure
    make
    sudo make install
The last command will ask for your password.
If "make" fails, try with:
    "./configure --without-xfilemanager" instead of "./configure"
If "sudo make install" fails try with:
    ./configure
    make
    su root
    make install
    exit


Non-technical users can ignore the rest.

Variables/options (for configure):
    --without-xfilemanager
    --with-<name_of_favorite_filemanager>
    --prefix
    --exec_prefix
    --bindir
    --datarootdir
    --docdir
    --infodir
    --htmldir
    --mandir
    --man1dir
    --man3dir
    --man5dir
    --man1ext
    --man3ext
    --man5ext
    --libdir
    --srcdir
    --DESTDIR
    --moduledir         Where to install Python modules
    --disable-gui
    --disable-guidoc
    --disable-cli
    --disable-techdoc   skogpasswdmanfiles(5), skogpasswdmanapi(1)
    --disable-rli
    --disable-rlidoc
    --halt              do nothing.
    --update            See 'configure.2'.
    --help              list things that are not used.
    --verbose
    --symlinks          old names
    --no-symlinks
